theorem
(H is_point_conv_on X implies (((( abs H ) is_point_conv_on X & ( lim (( abs H ),X) ) = ( abs ( lim (H,X) ) )) & ( - H ) is_point_conv_on X) & ( lim (( - H ),X) ) = ( - ( lim (H,X) ) )))
proof
assume A1: H is_point_conv_on X;
A2:now
let x;
assume x in X;
then ( H # x ) is  convergent by A1,CKB35:1;
then ( abs ( H # x ) ) is  convergent by SEQ_4:13;
hence ( ( abs H ) # x ) is  convergent by CKB49:1;
end;
A3:now
let x;
assume x in ( dom ( - ( lim (H,X) ) ) );
then A4: x in ( dom ( lim (H,X) ) ) by VALUED_1:8;
then x in X by A1,CKB37:def 1;
then A5: ( H # x ) is  convergent by A1,CKB35:1;
thus ( ( - ( lim (H,X) ) ) . x ) = ( - ( ( lim (H,X) ) . x ) ) by VALUED_1:8
.= ( - ( lim ( H # x ) ) ) by A1,A4,CKB37:def 1
.= ( lim ( - ( H # x ) ) ) by A5,SEQ_2:10
.= ( lim ( ( - H ) # x ) ) by CKB49:1;
end;
A6: X common_on_dom H by A1,CKB35:1;
then X common_on_dom ( abs H ) by CKB55:1;
hence A7: ( abs H ) is_point_conv_on X by A2,CKB35:1;
A8:now
let x;
assume x in ( dom ( abs ( lim (H,X) ) ) );
then A9: x in ( dom ( lim (H,X) ) ) by VALUED_1:def 11;
then x in X by A1,CKB37:def 1;
then A10: ( H # x ) is  convergent by A1,CKB35:1;
thus ( ( abs ( lim (H,X) ) ) . x ) = ( abs ( ( lim (H,X) ) . x ) ) by VALUED_1:18
.= ( abs ( lim ( H # x ) ) ) by A1,A9,CKB37:def 1
.= ( lim ( abs ( H # x ) ) ) by A10,SEQ_4:14
.= ( lim ( ( abs H ) # x ) ) by CKB49:1;
end;
A11:now
let x;
assume x in X;
then ( H # x ) is  convergent by A1,CKB35:1;
then ( - ( H # x ) ) is  convergent by SEQ_2:9;
hence ( ( - H ) # x ) is  convergent by CKB49:1;
end;
( dom ( abs ( lim (H,X) ) ) ) = ( dom ( lim (H,X) ) ) by VALUED_1:def 11
.= X by A1,CKB37:def 1;
hence ( lim (( abs H ),X) ) = ( abs ( lim (H,X) ) ) by A7,A8,CKB37:def 1;
X common_on_dom ( - H ) by A6,CKB55:1;
hence A12: ( - H ) is_point_conv_on X by A11,CKB35:1;
( dom ( - ( lim (H,X) ) ) ) = ( dom ( lim (H,X) ) ) by VALUED_1:8
.= X by A1,CKB37:def 1;
hence thesis by A12,A3,CKB37:def 1;
end;
